{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1678fd70-0979-47df-b237-260d852db2e9","content":"Yes, both are correct and still the standard approach in .NET MAUI on .NET 10.\n\n**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — Adjusts the page content to avoid the notch/Dynamic Island. You need the iOS platform-specific namespace:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\nOr in C#:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration;\nusing Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;\n\npage.On<iOS>().SetUseSafeArea(true);\n```\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"`** — Lets a specific layout extend *into* the unsafe area (behind the notch), even when the page uses safe area. Perfect for background images:\n\n```xml\n<Grid IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\">\n    <Image Source=\"background.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n</Grid>\n```\n\n**In short:** Use `UseSafeArea` on the page to protect your content, then selectively use `IgnoreSafeArea` on layouts where you want edge-to-edge visuals. Your tutorial's guidance is correct.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"20e030be-b904-4bb4-bc09-1b7009b3de99","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two properties:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - a platform-specific property for ContentPage\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - a property on Grid for background images\n\nLet me check what I know about these APIs in .NET MAUI, particularly for .NET 10.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the iOS safe area handling has evolved:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - This was the iOS platform-specific approach. In XAML, you'd use the `xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"` namespace and set `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`.\n\n\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea` - This property exists on certain layout types to allow content to extend into the safe area, which is useful for background images that should span the full screen. I need to verify the exact API surface for .NET 10, since the safe area handling approach has shifted over MAUI versions, and I should be careful about what's actually available versus what was in earlier previews. here. Let me think about what I know:\n\n- In .NET MAUI, `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` is the platform-specific way to handle safe areas on iOS\n- `IgnoreSafeArea` is a property available on layout views\n\nThese are well-established .NET MAUI APIs that should still be current for .NET 10. I'm confident enough to provide a direct answer with a practical XAML example showing how to use both properties together.","outputTokens":1117,"requestId":"9BC7:1605AB:60E3BB2:6C2EE7F:69EC11A6"},"id":"065f7cb5-60fa-413a-ab1a-c4512cf942a8","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:58:35.947Z","parentId":"5a62632a-1ff8-4941-af0a-4bab869fe4e2"}
